The quadratic equation can be written as 6(x - 11)^2 = 0 because (x - 11)^2 = x^2 - 22x + 121. So we have:

6(x - 11)^2 - 6*121 = 0 
6(x - 11)^2 = 6*6^2;
(x - 11)^2 = 6^2;
x - 11 = ±6;
x = 11 ±6 = 11 + 6,  11-6;
x = 17, 5. 

Therefore, the roots of the given quadratic equation are x = 17 and x = 5.
